triples.evidence: Bioluminescence is visible light generated by a living organism through a chemical reaction.
It’s sometimes called cold light, because it doesn’t involve heat like a light bulb does.

evidence: Scientists can isolate the light-emitting proteins from these organisms - the so-called bioluminescent proteins - and then combine them with other target molecules...
